# 🤖 Vision-Query Manager

# 🤖 Vision-Query AI Agent

📌 Overview  
This project is an AI system that processes images and answers user questions intelligently.  
It follows a complete pipeline:

• Image → Validation → Blur Detection → Query Parsing → Safety Check → Gemini AI → Output  

The system is designed as a **production-ready multimodal AI agent**.

---


---

## 📁 Project Structure

```
capston_project/
│
|__backend
       |__main.py                  # Agent entry point (full pipeline)
├── .env                     # API key (NOT committed to git)
├── images/                  # Folder containing input images (.jpg / .png)
│   └── sample.jpg
|__vision-query-ui
       |__src
          |__ App.jsx   # ui code 
├── requirements.txt         # All dependencies
├── README.md                # This file
```

---

## ⚙️ Setup Instructions

### Prerequisites

- Python 3.10+
- A valid [Google Gemini API Key](https://aistudio.google.com/app/apikey)

### Step 1 — Created folder

```bash
mkdir capston_project
```

### Step 2 — Create a Virtual Environment

```bash
python -m venv venv
venv\Scripts\activate
```

### Step 3 — Install Dependencies

```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

### Step 4 — Set Up Your API Key

Create a `.env` file in the root folder:

```
GEMINI_API_KEY=your_actual_key_here
```

### Step 5 — Add Your Images

Place `.jpg`, `.jpeg`, or `.png` images in the `images/` folder.  
Blurry images are automatically detected and skipped at startup.

### Step 6 — Run the Agent

```bash
python main.py
```

